<p>About an hour later, a school of mackerel came by and for about 20 minutes, we caught a fish every cast. They were driving the bait to the surface and the birds were also having a feast.</p>

<figure class="">
  <a href="/assets/images/2019/05/IMG_3480.jpg">
  <img src="/assets/images/2019/05/IMG_3480.jpg" alt="" />
  
    <figcaption>
      

    </figcaption></a></figure>

<p>We were hoping for a large fish (or a few more), but gave it our best shot. May is the start of the season with June/July being the most productive months. The best chance of big fish is in August and Conway fishes off Long Beach for them at that time. He catches them up to 300 lb, with larger ones being unstoppable and involves chasing the fish full speed with the boat. We were fortunately to catch one under difficult conditions. It was a great experience and we look forward to returning.</p>

:ET